                <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="70" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL" onselect="storeCaret(this);" onclick="storeCaret(this);" onkeyup="storeCaret(this);" onchange="storeCaret(this);">[quote][i]Originally posted by Darkray16[/i]
[br]hes not trying to say all should do exactly what he says. hes just trying to make you guys think about the NBG system more.  and the name need before greed implies that its a fair system when its not at all.  I keep trying to convince my guild that this system isn't fair at all.  that platinum has as good a chance of being used as an upgrade as a droppable.  for isntance whose to say that droppable item isn't gonna be sold by the person whoc an use it, or who can say what a person is gonna be using his plat on.  most people make a huge and mistaken assumption that droppable gear is always going to be used when they think about the NBG system.  after trying to explain this to them I was called greedy...yea like I got a better chance of getting those FT3 boots now that the entire guild is bidding on them with their dkp points.  I keep telling them that I keep trying to make my point because I know I am rite.  their ignorance makes me want to cry.  anyways yea thats my thought on it.
