    <td>
      <table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center">
        <tr>
          <td bgcolor="black">
            <table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="4">
              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="" colspan="2" align="center"><b><font face="verdana" size="1" color="mintcream">T O P I C&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;R E V I E W</font></b></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#37437B" valign="top" width="100" nowrap><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2"><b>Laeelin</b></font></td>
                <td bgcolor="#37437B" valign="top" width="100%"><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;12/12/2003&nbsp;: 11:47:01 AM</small><hr size="1"><span class="spnMessageText"> Well, i'm reposting this because it was lost and I want to hear what people think.. <br /><br />NBG = The great Myth<br /><br />99% of all groups use a system called "NBG" (Need Before Greed) to decide who gets an item when it drops. It's a system thats easy to explain.<br /><br />If you would equip an item, then you can roll on it.<br /><br />You cant get any easier than that to explain. It sounds like a very fair system and thats one of the reasons it's so popular. The idea is that sometimes wiz casters will be the ones rolling.. Sometimes int casters.. sometimes tanks.. sometimes pure melee.. sometimes just one class would roll on an item. But over time you would roll it would balance out.<br /><br />This system sounds very fair.<br /><br />Thats the great myth.<br /><br />NBG is actually an unfair system. It's also a system thats easy to abuse. NBG looks fair at first glance, but on a closer look you will (hopefully) see it for what it is. To attempt to explain i'm going to make up an imaginary group and place them in a few situations.<br /><br />Imagine this group:<br /><br />1) Warrior (uber gear)<br />2) Pally (average gear)<br />3) Rogue (average gear)<br />4) Necro (average gear - the one that formed the group)<br />5) Beastlord (good gear)<br />6) Cleric (Great gear - Farms all the time, in VERY good droppable gear)<br /><br />Lets Imagine 2 diffrent situations.<br /><br />a) FT3 boots camp in CT.<br />b) BoT towers hopeing for ornate.<br /><br />In situation (a), When the boots drop only one person would be rolling on them. The necro. Thats the only person in the group that would actualy use the boots, so they get defaulted to him under NBG.<br /><br />In situation (b)..<br />Leather drops: Monk and Beastlord roll.<br />Silk drops: Necro rolls.<br />Plate drops: Pally rolls<br />Chain: Rogue rolls.<br /><br />Now at first glance this looks fair, but when you loot closer you will see that it isnt fair at all. <br /><br />For one thing, The necro that formed the group abused the system by makeing sure that no one in the group could use the items he wanted so he made sure the group didnt get another silk wearer.. Thats one problem with the NBG system... It's easy to abuse.. just make sure you form the group and that you form it with people that will not be rolling on the same stuff you are. (note: this assumes that the necro formed the group that way delibertatly)<br /><br />The cleric didnt get the FT3 boots because she farmed an insane amount of cash for the Ornate Plate Boots.. She cant now recover some of the cash she sunk into thoes boots by selling the FT3 boots because of NBG. <br /><br />The first camp droped something that could have sold for 80k, but only the necro had a chance to get it, everyone else walked away with nothing. They deserve the same chance of getting an upgrade!<br /><br />The second camp dropped something for everyone but the cleric and warrior. Both of them put in the same work and time.. They deserve the same chance of getting an upgrade!<br /><br />===================================================<br /><br />NBG is the welfare system of EQ.<br /><br />Thoes who have done more work/time/whatever supporting thoes who have not.<br /><br />Now before you think i'm being mean with that statement, really think about it and tell me it's not true.<br /><br />Many people only play a couple hours a week, many had RL stuff come up and had to take a break from EQ for a while.. They deserve the same chance that everyone else has... not a better chance than anyone else.<br /><br />It's not that thoes that play more and have better gear are "better" or "deserve" it more... it's that they deserve the SAME chance.<br /><br />I dont think that I should get more than you because i'm poorer than you, and I also dont think that I should get more because i'm richer than you.<br /><br />I support equil rights.<br /><br />I dont support the unfairness that is NBG.. <br /><br />Not when I'm the only int caster and everything would default to me and when it doesnt.<br /><br />I just want to use a fair system.<br /><br />go go gravy!<br /><br /></span></font></td>
