 nowrap><b><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2">Saminga</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#37437B" valign="top"><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;12/13/2003&nbsp;: 6:07:03 PM</small><hr size="1"><span class="spnMessageText"> Ultimately, what you need in loot disputes is an independant arbiter to make the judgement. Unless you have specifically factored out ALL the variables in the equation, it's a crapshoot of what classes will be in your group, what camp you will get, who is going to use it and who is going to sell it, who actually needs it since they are a poor ass player that is a nice person, for example. If you take out these variables, and go "Hey, we are going to camp the Copper Hammer of Striking for Arione coz he needs one" then, go to it.<br /><br />In a pick up group, there are so many variables you don't know, that coming in with a preconceived idea like NBG when you don't have all the factors at your command, you cannot, not even the geniuses of the world, make a proper judgement without that information. It's not like we can tell how much cash people have in the bank, whether this is their main or a twink, how many accounts they have and stuff. We simply don't know, so no matter how objective we can be, we cannot truly be a proper arbiter for a "fair" system, NBG or otherwise.<br /><br />In DKP, there is a strict account of how much you have put into the guild, and how much you can get from it, by comparison. This doesn't take into anyone's details on how good their character is equipped, but considering it really only applies to no drop gear for the most part, people aren't going to waste their DKP on something they can't use.<br /><br />When we roll on something, we leave Chance as the final arbiter. Chance is a bitch, but ultimately fair, coz unless someone can load the dice in EQ, it's really not up to anyone who gets the item, ergo it's a level playing field.<br /><br />As someone else suggested, if you win something, you can be an arbiter of justice and give it away, as your choice. However, this choice is *not* forced upon you, it is completely up to the individual whether they wish to make these choices. And the associated karma. Forced virtue has no virtue.<br /><br />For the record ... I transferred Saminga and lost all her gear. I don't expect NBG, even though I am sorely lacking in equipment, and I lost all my hard earned DKP loot in the transfer. And I still oppose NBG. I don't expect a handout simply because I am a transfer, what I at least want is an opportunity to roll on an item I can use. I can live with that.<br /><br />Saminga Amaranth, 65th Deathbitch Spankmistress.</span></font></td>
