, too bad. A compassionate system would help them despite the fact that they screwed up.<br /><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />There is a huge diffrence between someone who "screwed" themselves in RL, and someone who has lower end gear for there level...<br /><br />In RL, you cant always go back and fix things.<br /><br />But in EQ, i dont care if your a nude rogue at level 65... You can still farm spiderling silks and low quality hides and in a couple weeks reach a reasonable level of gear.. And then start groups at areas with good drops to either upgrade, or sell well...<br /><br />But in RL, a single mom with 3 kids, can NEVER reach what someone with a masters in whatever makeing 250k a year is makeing.<br /><br />She just cant do it unless poeple are willing to give her a lot of help.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br />Laeelin, in EQ there is such a thing as "being born poor." It doesn't work quite like in RL, however. For instance, let's say that a level 65 necro in Time gear with 500k+ pp starts a twink. Obviously, this twink is far more "fortunate" than anyone of the same level. Now consider someone who just started EQ and has exactly jack. His character is obviously far "poorer" than the twink.<br /><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />No, he isnt poorer that that other player started at... sure if you want to take someone with 200 /played days and compair one of his twinks to someone with 0 /played days that twink will be better off.. but the PLAYER have been better off when that player had 0 /played days.</span></font></td>
